# C++ QKD Production Standards

For C++ in QKD/defense contexts:

- Never log key material, nonces, IVs, or credentials — CRITICAL invariant
- Mutex must protect specific state — document which mutex guards what
- RAII only; smart pointers; noexcept destructors
- For networking: always handle reconnect and mid-message failure
- C++17 minimum — verify before suggesting patterns
- Use `cpp-engineer` skill for implementation, `cpp-review` for audits

Security lens requires threat model before architecture changes.
